SpiceSynth includes the following third-party software:

================================================================================
Nuked-OPL3
================================================================================

Description:  Cycle-accurate OPL3 (YMF262) emulator
Version:      1.8
Author:       Nuke.YKT
Copyright:    Copyright (C) 2013-2020 Nuke.YKT
License:      GNU Lesser General Public License v2.1 or later (LGPL-2.1-or-later)
Source:       https://github.com/nukeykt/Nuked-OPL3
Location:     chip/opl3/opl3.c, chip/opl3/opl3.h
License file: chip/opl3/COPYING

The Nuked-OPL3 C source is vendored unmodified and statically compiled into
this library via CGo. Because the complete source is included in the repository,
users who build from source can freely modify and recompile the LGPL component.
If you distribute pre-compiled binaries that incorporate this library, you must
comply with LGPL-2.1 Section 6 by providing the LGPL source code and a
mechanism for relinking (e.g., object files or build instructions).

================================================================================
DMXOPL
================================================================================

Description:  YMF262-enhanced FM patch set for Doom and source ports
Author:       sneakernets
Copyright:    Copyright (c) 2017 sneakernets
License:      MIT License
Source:       https://github.com/sneakernets/DMXOPL
Location:     op2/GENMIDI.op2

The DMXOPL GENMIDI bank file is embedded in the op2 package and provides
General MIDI instrument definitions (128 melodic + 47 percussion) for OPL2/OPL3
FM synthesis. The file is included unmodified under the MIT license.

================================================================================
AdPlug
================================================================================

Description:  AdLib sound player library
Authors:      Simon Peter, Torbjorn Andersson, Johannes Schickel (ScummVM)
Copyright:    Copyright (C) 1999-2024 Simon Peter et al.
License:      GNU Lesser General Public License v2.1 or later (LGPL-2.1-or-later)
Source:       https://github.com/adplug/adplug
Location:     adl/ (Go port of src/adl.cpp and src/adl.h)

The adl package is a Go port of AdPlug's ADL player (adl.cpp/adl.h), which
implements the Westwood Studios ADL music format used in Dune II. The original
C++ code was ported to Go with equivalent logic. No original C/C++ source is
included — this is a clean reimplementation in Go. The port preserves the
original LGPL-2.1 license for the derived work.
